node.text: Dr. Mary Clifton @marycliftonmd joins host Danny Brasco @dbrasco91 to debunk some marijuana myths 🤯🌿 Discuss her best-selling book “The Grass is Greener” and her professional certification program 🤓 🥦📚And talk about her experience going from teen mom to world-famous medical cannabis expert 👩‍👧👩🏼‍⚕️

node.title: Globally Renowned Dr. Mary Clifton Debunks Some Marijuana Myths

node.text: Host Danny Brasco @dbrasco91 is joined by medical Cannabis pioneer Dr. Joseph Rosado @dr.josephrosado to discuss his groundbreaking work with Cannabis in the state of Florida 🌿🍊His book Hope & Healing: The Case for Cannabis 🙏🏽🥦📚His stance on Cannabis as a treatment for Covid-19 🤔😷 A wonderful success story of how Cannabis helped treat PTSD and changed a war veteran’s life 🌳🇺🇸and so much more. Next up for Dr. Rosado... An exploration into the benefits of psychedelics ✌🏽🍄 And can cannabis cure erectile dysfunction??? 👀 Stay tuned

node.title: Dr. Joseph Rosado Drops Knowledge On The Healing Power of Medical Cannabis

node.text: Culinary Cannabis. It’s been around for a long time, but just recently has it become mainstream and a big part of the cannabis industry. This delicious Green Eggs & Ham recipe was created by the authors (@frauleinchef & @getmellows) from the best selling cannabis cookbook EDIBLES: Small Bites for the Modern Cannabis Kitchen and we are excited to announce that @frauleinchef will be joining us LIVE tomorrow at 4:20pm EST to talk everything Culinary Cannabis & more. She is the cannabis chef winner of the new @netflix series 'Cooked with Cannabis‘ and has been named one of America’s Top 10 Cannabis Chefs. In 2015 she founded, what is now the longest running monthly cannabis pop up Restaurant in the world @cannaisseurseries . And now during the pandemic she has begun offering infused meal kits in the Bay Area, CA. Come learn about culinary cannabis and more during our live. See you then!

Do you know someone living with PCOS? Be sure to share this helpful information with them! CBD may provide the healing powers necessary to help PCOS patients find relief. The cannabinoids from cannabis products, such as CBD, can modulate the body by supplementing it with the cannabinoids it needs. 

Learn more here and get started with a medical card in your state on our website. Link in bio.
